article.headline: W. Michigan 69, Toledo 55
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- David Kool scored 24 points and Western Michigan rode a 19-4 run to finish the first half to a 69-55 victory over Toledo on Saturday night. Shawntes Gary added 14 points and 11 rebounds and Andrew Hershberger had 12 points for the Broncos (18-10, 11-3 Mid-American Conference). Tyrone Kent had 14 points, Jerrah Young 11 and Jonathan Amos 10 for the Rockets, who led 20-18 with 7:36 left in the opening half. But then Kool tied the game with a jumper to spark a 15-0 run that included 3-pointers by Andre Ricks and Kool. Kool had seven points in that spurt as Toledo went scoreless for just over 5 minutes. The lead never fell below 10 points again.
